Fry Bread & Beer Cheese ü§§ü§§ü§§
Beer Battered Walleye could not have been better. And the Miss Piggy Burger with pork and cheese, tasted like quality barbecued ribs on a burger that was very good!
Walking in at 5:30 for fish fry on a Friday night was an hour wait but it was worth it. The atmosphere is really nice. Cozy yet trendy remodel with high ceilings and lots of windows in the dining area at the back of the building.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrL8i_w2suUUPrEKW7psgGn6hSakjhRfDvRvl8&fid=0x0:0x5ccde4784b50a38d"],"When":"2025-1-25"},{"Name":"Monica Abraham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4BZp063N8s6ziRJrsOgoMFUG7OZnGvjSAAg7dC2DFEOFBpfu7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This bar/restaurant is incredible. The atmosphere is great and every member of the staff was so friendly! The food was incredible too. I have never been to a bar that had lobster in so many dishes. I got the street corn nachos and added lobster and it was the best meal I have ever eaten! My husband had the lobster croissant and it was a heaping pile of lobster on a delicious croissant. We will drive the 40 minutes from home just to eat here again!!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNw9OG47vBRKd7jAmOt2ho99KggHjFwrC958Oyq&fid=0x0:0x5ccde4784b50a38d"],"When":"2023-4-22"},{"Name":"Katie Lemke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJjEvdjdCV4JpjaT7gYzYBPsXnZRJBYxZXauDosVgLDaKHoxRJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food! Love the variety. The deep fried balls with cheese are legit the best. The menu prices are competitive and honestly it cost us more to eat at fast food so we elect for good food! But love the remodel and it looks small from the outside but once you walk in you‚Äôll be pleasantly surprised by the amount of room and kid friendly they are! Don‚Äôt be afraid to make this your next dinner spot. Definitely worth the effort.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP57L2kJMAPzfCmVv45KhQPifZT5f7uCWKy7D3d&fid=0x0:0x5ccde4784b50a38d"],"When":"2024-5-28"},{"Name":"Sheanon Riley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_97JTOJiu3WLeoW-VCLglKRfGLOt1EMNAtAK0AzzNcli0IQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolute treasure. Right off Rte. 29, walking distance from Wilderness Crossing Travel Center. Staff is welcoming and friendly and the place as a whole is clearly a labor of love. Inside and outside, it's like being at your best friends home. An eclectic mixup, best attributes of a dive bar and an upscale gastropub. I missed the kitchen closing time, but the bar itself did not disappoint. Beer selection was great, liquor selection was exceptional. Places like this are few and far between, understandable because Rachel's outshines them all! Again, can't say enough about the staff. Ashley and Caitlin (so sorry of I spelled it wrong!) are phenomenal!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOai2ekGGnDJgCUsIgRsi6G9Ts9I9zUlJWuxEhb&fid=0x0:0x5ccde4784b50a38d"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Karwowski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQ3FC0t76mmXrMIg7a5X4h17LSDWpJMxuPZr21kTY7IbKJOJg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really like this stop on the road up north. It's the first time I've ever seen a pool table outside! I was treated well by the staff very friendly! It's worth a look there's an outside beer garden type thing where you could sit outside and order. I seen a lot of motorcyclists there so it's popular with the
two wheelers

I did not eat there because I was in between meals arrived at the wrong time to eat. So I can't speak about the food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Craig & Bernice","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVb1Q_ZD_HW5ZxjHgCawlUhnYflL15aLgyhdFkdK4HG0TRNQ6bD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We absolutely love this pace and the bartenders are top notch.. On our way back down from north woods we love to stop
For lunch.. Menu is great a variety for everyone!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOB9M1zH3gnFAmVb6HvYJaW4FvtyFktu9U6I_c&fid=0x0:0x5ccde4784b50a38d"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Kimberly C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7TwCMJY7LyBcRgnh2ESpp6pS2mnuNe_RG5b2sRMXiq6uDFPUl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a cool place. Saw the sign on 29 and decided to check it out. There is a patio and I saw patrons with their pups! Service was excellent; server explained immediately that there would be a delay with food orders, but the appetizers came out fairly quickly and the drinks were almost immediate.

Get the cheese curds!

Food is good and the menu is creative, you've got pub staples like burgers, and then you have fun stuff, like lobster tacos! Yum. Oh and a Thai curry soup  was divine.

There's tabletop and others games as well as ongoing trivia on television screens. Even the bathroom is cool.

Great place to hang out with good food and a cool atmosphere. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kate Chartrand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIV2miBjLhIXiDyRSK0Cnxcqpf-BvdtiALWqacSC4-puO9z3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent lunch while traveling through! Very clean bar & grill, friendly staff, outdoor seating available. I had the Cuban croissant sandwich & my husband had the bacon bourbon burger with beer fries, both meals really tasty!","Images":null,"When":""}]
